transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, hey, I had an order that I ordered with you guys, and you guys sent me the wrong stuff.

Speaker 1: Okay, good to know.

Speaker 2: I was supposed to get in.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: What's your last name on the zip code?

Speaker 1: Last name is Reed, R-E-E-D.

Speaker 2: Zip code is 3-0-2-4-8.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I pulled up your profile here, sir.

Speaker 1: I do want to mention that currently I see your prescriptions written out for the Viagra AGB,

Speaker 2: but what does the ingredient on the pill you received say on there?

Speaker 1: Not a lot.

Speaker 2: I'll see if I can light to this thing, see if I can see it.

Speaker 1: Hold on.

Speaker 2: I've got to get a pair of reading glasses.

Speaker 1: I can't see this.

Speaker 2: Okay, it's A-C-3-3-9.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: With that information, I can confirm the pharmacy made a mistake.

Speaker 1: The only engraving you should have seen on your pill is 50 for the dosage and nothing else.

Speaker 2: I'm going to go ahead and notify the pharmacy, and that way we can ship you a brand-new order.

Speaker 1: You'll receive it in three to four business days.

Speaker 2: Aside from that, the one you received, you're more than welcome to keep, use, or dispose of,

Speaker 1: but we'll send you the correct one.

Speaker 2: Okay, but they're going to send me the one that I ordered, right, not some generic?

Speaker 1: Exactly.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: Of course.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: All right.
